    • Field Detail

      • MAX_MAGNITUDE

        public static final java.math.BigInteger MAX_MAGNITUDE
        The maximum integer supported by Fynotek's number system. You can compare if a number x is too large or small with (x.abs().compareTo(MAX_MAGNITUDE) > 0).
        See Also:
        number(BigInteger)

    • Constructor Detail

      • FynotekWord

        public FynotekWord​(java.lang.String word,
                   boolean isProper)
        Converts a String and a boolean into a FynotekWord. The String contains the word itself, while the boolean represents whether the word is a proper noun: true if it is, and false if it is not.
        Parameters:
        word - word to be converted to a FynotekWord.
        isProper - whether the word is a proper noun or not.

      • FynotekWord

        public FynotekWord​(java.lang.String word)
        Converts a String into a FynotekWord. The word is assumed not to be a proper noun.
        Parameters:
        word - word to be converted to a FynotekWord.

      • nounCase

        public FynotekWord nounCase​(char caseOfNoun)
        Returns this FynotekWord inflected for the noun case specified by caseOfNoun. caseOfNoun should be either 'n' (nominative), 'a' (accusative), 'g' (genitive), or 'd' (dative). All other charcters will cause the original object to be returned.
        Parameters:
        caseOfNoun - the noun case to inflect this FynotekWord for.
        Returns:
        this FynotekWord inflected for the specified noun case.

      • verbTense

        public FynotekWord verbTense​(char tenseOfVerb,
                             boolean hypothetical)
        Returns this FynotekWord inflected for the verb tense specified by tenseOfVerb. tenseOfVerb should be either 'p' (present), 'a' (past), 'f' (future), or 'g' (gnomic). All other charcters will cause the original object to be returned. If hypothetical is set to true, the word will be marked for a hypothetical tense; otherwise, the word will be inflected for a non-hypothetical tense.
        Parameters:
        tenseOfVerb - the verb tense to inflect this FynotekWord for.
        hypothetical - whether this word should be inflected for a hypothetical tense or not.
        Returns:
        this FynotekWord inflected for the specified verb tense.

      • verbTense

        public FynotekWord verbTense​(char tenseOfVerb)
        Returns this FynotekWord inflected for the non-hypothetical verb tense specified by tenseOfVerb. tenseOfVerb should be either 'p' (present), 'a' (past), 'f' (future), or 'g' (gnomic). All other charcters will cause the original object to be returned.
        Parameters:
        tenseOfVerb - the verb tense to inflect this FynotekWord for.
        Returns:
        this FynotekWord inflected for the specified verb tense.

      • suffix

        public FynotekWord suffix​(java.lang.String suffix)
        Returns a FynotekWord with the specified suffix appended to the end of this word. If the suffix creates a phonotactically invalid sequence, n or a will be infixed as needed to make the resulting word phonotactically valid.
        Parameters:
        suffix - the suffix to be appended to the end of this FynotekWord.
        Returns:
        a FynotekWord with the specified suffix appended to the end of it.
        See Also:
        prefix(String)

      • marked

        public boolean marked()
        Returns whether this FynotekWord has been marked previously or not. To be specific, this function returns true if and only if this word was created as an output from the nounCase or verbTense method. You can use this method to make sure a word does not get marked more than once.
        Returns:
        a FynotekWord with the specified suffix appended to the end of it.
        See Also:
        nounCase(char), verbTense(char,boolean)

      • isProper

        public boolean isProper()
        Returns whether this FynotekWord is a proper noun or not. Specifically, this returns true if this word is a proper noun, and false if it is not.
        Returns:
        whether this FynotekWord is a proper noun or not.
        See Also:

      • number

        public static java.lang.String number​(java.math.BigInteger num)
        Returns the Fynotek translation of the specified number. If the number's absolute value is greater than MAX_MAGNITUDE, an empty String is returned.
        Parameters:
        num - the number to be translated.
        Returns:
